#: ../../../development/testing.md:3
msgid "Testing and benchmarking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:5
msgid "Testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:7
msgid "Running the Python test suite"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:9
msgid ""
"Install the following dependencies into the default Python installation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:11
msgid "pip install pytest-pyodide pytest-httpserver\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:15
msgid ""
"`pytest-pyodide` is a pytest plugin for testing Pyodide and third-party "
"applications that use Pyodide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:18
msgid ""
"See: [pytest-pyodide](https://github.com/pyodide/pytest-pyodide) for more "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:20
msgid ""
"Install [geckodriver](https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases) or "
"[chromedriver](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/chromedriver/downloads) and "
"check that they are in your `PATH`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:24
msgid "To run the test suite, run `pytest` from the root directory of Pyodide:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:26
msgid "pytest\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:30
msgid "There are 2 test locations that are collected by pytest,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:32
msgid ""
"`src/tests/`: general Pyodide tests and tests running the CPython test suite"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:33
msgid "`packages/*/test_*`: package specific tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:35
msgid "You can run the tests from a specific file with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:37
msgid "pytest path/to/test/file.py\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:41
msgid ""
"Some browsers sometimes produce informative errors than others so if you are "
"getting confusing errors it is worth rerunning the test on each browser. You "
"can use `--runtime` commandline option to specify the browser runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:45
msgid ""
"pytest --runtime firefox\n"
"pytest --runtime chrome\n"
"pytest --runtime node\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:51
msgid "Custom test marks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:53
msgid "We support custom test marks:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:55
msgid ""
"`@pytest.mark.skip_refcount_check` and `pytest.mark.skip_pyproxy_check` "
"disable respectively the check for JavaScript references and the check for "
"PyProxies. If a test creates JavaScript references or PyProxies and does not "
"clean them up, by default the tests will fail. If a test is known to leak "
"objects, it is possible to disable these checks with these markers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:61
msgid "Running the JavaScript test suite"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:63
msgid ""
"To run tests on the JavaScript Pyodide package, run the following commands,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:66
msgid ""
"cd src/js\n"
"npm test\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:71
msgid "To check TypeScript type definitions run,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:73
msgid "npx tsd\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:79
msgid "Manual interactive testing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:81
msgid "To run tests manually:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:83
msgid "Build Pyodide, perhaps in the docker image"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:85
msgid ""
"From outside of the docker image, `cd` into the `dist` directory and run "
"`python -m http.server`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:88
msgid ""
"Once the webserver is running, simple interactive testing can be run by "
"visiting the URL: `http://localhost:<PORT>/console.html`. It's recommended "
"to use `pyodide.runPython` in the browser console rather than using the repl."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:92
msgid "Benchmarking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:94
msgid ""
"To run common benchmarks to understand Pyodide's performance, begin by "
"installing the same prerequisites as for testing. Then run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:97
msgid "PYODIDE_PACKAGES=\"numpy,matplotlib\" make benchmark\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:101
msgid "Linting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:103
msgid "We lint with `prek`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:105
msgid ""
"Python is linted with `ruff` (for linting and formatting) and `mypy`. "
"JavaScript and TypeScript are linted with `biome`. C is linted with `clang-"
"format`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:109
msgid "To lint the code, run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:111
msgid "prek -a\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:115
msgid ""
"You can have the linter automatically run whenever you commit by running"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:117
msgid ""
"pip install prek\n"
"prek install\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:122
msgid "and this can later be disabled with"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:124
msgid "prek uninstall\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/testing.md:128
msgid ""
"If you don't lint your code, certain lint errors will be fixed automatically "
"by `pre-commit.ci` which will push fixes to your branch. If you want to push "
"more commits, you will either have to pull in the remote changes or force "
"push."
msgstr ""
